    "## 2. Combining methods helps — but only up to a point\n",
    "\n",
    "Since different methods are best on different samples, the natural\n",
    "next step is to combine them. We built a simple **dispatcher** (call\n",
    "it **C5**): for each brain, use the method known to work best for\n",
    "that density of cells. On sparse brains, defer to the method with\n",
    "highest confidence. On dense brains, prefer the graph matcher.\n",
    "On medium brains, prefer the geometric matcher.\n",
    "\n",
    "C5 is our current best. Summing its match rate across all six\n",
    "brains gives **1.08** (a score between 0 and 6). This is the\n",
    "\"ceiling\" for any method that only looks at cell positions."
   ]
