    "## 3. Two brains we still can't match above 0\n",
    "\n",
    "Look at sample **782149** — every method scores **zero** on it.\n",
    "Why? Because this brain has three strikes against it:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. The tissue is **tilted by about 12°** out of plane,\n",
    "2. The 3D image is **unusually thin** (less than a millimetre deep),\n",
    "3. Only **34%** of its cells have a matching partner in the other image\n",
    "   (much lower than the usual 50–85%).\n",
    "\n",
    "At that combination, there isn't enough geometric signal for *any*\n",
    "method that only looks at cell positions to find the correct offset.\n",
    "The search basically has no handles to grip onto. We believe this\n",
    "sample is **structurally unreachable** without additional information\n",
