    "## 4. The consensus-voting idea that *should* have worked but didn't\n",
    "\n",
    "Our three best methods (P1, P4, P6) agree with each other on some\n",
    "cells and disagree on others. A reasonable intuition: **when two or\n",
    "more methods independently pick the same answer, that answer is\n",
    "probably right.**\n",
    "\n",
    "We measured this directly. On a single-cell basis:\n",
    "\n",
    "| sample  | 1 method votes | 2 methods agree | 3 methods agree |\n",
    "|---------|----------------|-----------------|-----------------|\n",
    "| 788406  | 17% correct    | 22% correct     | 28% correct     |\n",
    "| 790322  | 15% correct    | 34% correct     | 41% correct     |\n",
    "| 767018  | 17% correct    | 30% correct     | 33% correct     |\n",
    "\n",
    "So 2-method agreement is genuinely **1.3× to 2.2× more accurate**\n",
    "than a single vote. The signal is real."
