    "### Why did majority voting lose?\n",
    "\n",
    "The \"2 methods agree → more accurate\" statistic is **true on average**,\n",
    "but it pools together two different situations:\n",
    "\n",
    "- *All three methods agree* — these picks really are very accurate,\n",
    "  and C5 already uses them (the priority dispatcher picks the same\n",
    "  answer).\n",
    "- *Only two methods agree and the third disagrees* — these are the\n",
    "  cases where C6 actually **overrides** C5. And here, the disagreeing\n",
    "  method (P1, the geometric outlier filter) is often **right**, and\n",
    "  the two agreeing methods share the same **systematic error**.\n",
    "\n",
    "In other words: when P1 disagrees with P4 and P6, it's usually because\n",
    "P1's stricter filter has correctly rejected a pair that P4 and P6\n",
    "agreed on for the wrong reason. Forcing the majority to win throws\n",
    "away P1's best picks.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Lesson:** averaging across all 2-vote pairs hides the fact that\n",
    "the disagreement subset behaves completely differently from the\n",
    "unanimous subset."
   ]
  },
